
                                            The host country will be announced in November.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa will lead a high-level delegation to London at the weekend to present South Africa's bid to host the Rugby World Cup in 2023.  The host country will be announced in November. Ramaphosa's presence there will affirm government's support and commitment to return the tournament to the continent.  Spokesperson Tyrone Seal says: “We are hopeful that for the presentation South Africa will really make a good impression and that from that moment on we look forward to the announcement in November.”  (Edited by Refilwe Thobega)